084X.statement:
Notation and assumptions as in Situation @[084W]. If
\begin{enumerate}
\item $f$ is universally injective,
\item $f_0$ is locally of finite type,
\end{enumerate}
then $f_i$ is universally injective for some $i \geq 0$.

